To all the Guys:<br>
     All of you have good points!!!  Each person has a opinion and a right to it.  I agree, I myself don't like people &quot;preaching&quot; to me and forcing their view point as the only view point.  The only bit of advice I have to all of us that write on this forum, is to watch the language.  A honest discussion is necessary and is what a dialog is all about, but as a school teacher, by regulation I can't have my students view this website if it contains bad language.  It falls under our regulations over appropriate media.  All I ask is to PLEASE curb nasty language.  Say what your heart feels, just watch the adjectives.  This way schools can have students view this site.  Thanks for listening guys!!
<p><code>--   (Joe D.) </code><p>


